Guidelines for Requesting Row-Level Formulas
A row-level formula evaluates each record in a report, with the results of the formula shown in each report row. Each report supports one row-level formula. Describe the formula you want in simple terms, be as specific as possible about the details, name fields and functions if possible.

To give you more ideas about how to create useful formulas, here are some common requests and their responses:

Calculate profit margin as a percentage
(ssot__SalesOrder__dlm.ssot__GrandTotalAmount__c - ssot__SalesOrder__dlm.ssot__Cost__c) / ssot__SalesOrder__dlm.ssot__Cost__c * 100

Create a Full Name field that combines the contact first name and last name fields
ssot__Individual__dlm.ssot__FirstName__c + ' ' + ssot__Individual__dlm.ssot__LastName__c

Help me group any opportunity amounts larger than 100,000 as BIG, for amounts that are bigger than 10,000 as MEDIUM, SMALL for the rest
IF(Opportunity_Sales__dlm.Amount__c > 100000, 'BIG', IF(Opportunity_Sales__dlm.Amount__c > 10000, 'MEDIUM', 'SMALL'))

Is the Close Date past due?
IF(IF(apa_AgentWork__dlm.CloseDateTime__c < TODAY(), TRUE, FALSE), "TRUE", "FALSE")

Number of days between start date and close date
apa_AgentWork__dlm.CloseDateTime__c - apa_AgentWork__dlm.RequestDateTime__c

Sum total answer time for each row so that handle time and speed to answer are considered
apa_AgentWork__dlm.HandleTimeSeconds__c + apa_AgentWork__dlm.SpeedToAnswerSeconds__c
title: Requesting Row-Level Formulas
